getModuleRelativeFile

public static java.io.File getModuleRelativeFile(java.lang.Class<?> clazz,
                                                 java.lang.String filename)
Finds a file in the same module as the given class. For example, say you have a package named web and you need to refer to web/src/main/foo/bar. Pass this method a class that's in that module (i.e., compiled into web/target/test-classes) and src/main/foo/bar to get the path to the local copy of web/src/main/foo/bar.

Parameters:
clazz - A class from the desired module
filename - Path to the desired file, relative to the module root
